1. What is an NGFW

A Next-Generation Firewall is not just port/IP based.

It understands:

Applications

Users

Content

Threat behavior

It operates mainly at:

Layer 3–7

2. NGFW Architecture
          ┌──────────────┐
Internet ─┤ Outside Zone │
          └──────┬───────┘
                 │
         ┌───────▼────────┐
         │   NGFW Engine   │
         │ ────────────── │
         │  App ID        │
         │  User ID       │
         │  IPS           │
         │  AV            │
         │  SSL Inspect   │
         │  URL Filter    │
         └───────┬────────┘
                 │
          ┌──────▼───────┐
          │ Inside Zone  │
          └──────────────┘


Key idea:
Traffic is not allowed just because port 443 is open — it must match policy + application + user + security profile.

3. Why NGFW Is Needed

Traditional firewall problem:

Allowed TCP 443 = everything allowed

NGFW solution:

TCP 443 + App = HTTPS + URL + user + threat scan
